<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!-- Signed-release entitlements for cef_host (browser) + all CEF helper
       processes. Deliberately the MINIMAL set — omits get-task-allow (notarization
       hard-fail + task-port escalation vector for distributables) and, unlike the
       dev/ad-hoc entitlements.plist, drops every relaxation that isn't load-bearing
       in a signed build. Selected automatically by the build when CEF_HOST_ADHOC=OFF
       (see CMakeLists.txt / build_cef_host.sh).
       The renderer and GPU helpers JIT JavaScript / WebAssembly, so they keep
       allow-jit (MAP_JIT). We intentionally do NOT carry:
         - disable-library-validation: a dylib-injection -> entitlement-theft vector;
           single-identity inside-out signing (framework -> cef_host -> app) keeps
           library validation satisfied without it, so it's dev-only.
         - allow-unsigned-executable-memory: strictly broader than allow-jit and
           deprecated on macOS 14+; V8/MAP_JIT works with just allow-jit (Mozilla
           ships V8 the same way), so it's dev-only.
         - device.camera / device.audio-input: camera/mic are now gated by the
           deny-default CefPermissionHandler, so untrusted page content can't reach
           them and the OS-level entitlement buys nothing here. -->
  <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key><true/>
  <!-- Bluetooth is load-bearing: caBLE / hybrid passkeys (WebAuthn cross-device)
       reach Web Bluetooth, so this stays even in the minimal release set. -->
  <key>com.apple.security.device.bluetooth</key><true/>
</dict>
</plist>
